FF) List of all needed things
Pre-Requirements for Production Server (Option B)
1. Domain Name
You need a NEW domain (separate from amigor.top to avoid conflicts)

Options:

Buy a new domain on any registrar (Namecheap, Google Domains, etc.)

OR use a subdomain like matrix.yourdomain.com on a new domain you control

Cost: ~$10-15/year

2. DNS Setup
Point the domain's DNS A record to your public IP address (where you'll host globally)

Add SRV records for Matrix federation (optional but recommended):

text
_matrix._tcp.yourdomain.com SRV 10 0 8448 yourdomain.com
3. HTTPS Certificate
Get a free SSL certificate from Let's Encrypt (automatic with nginx)

OR buy one from a certificate authority

4. Public IP / Port Forwarding
Your server needs a static public IP or dynamic DNS

Forward ports 80 and 443 to your local server for HTTPS/HTTP

Forward port 8448 for Matrix federation (optional)

5. Database Backup Strategy
Backup your current PostgreSQL database before migrating globally

Keep separate backups of amigor.top data and new server data

6. Email Configuration (Optional but Recommended)
For password resets, notifications, etc.

Options:

SendGrid (free tier available)

AWS SES

Your own mail server

Or disable for testing

7. Matrix Accounts
Create admin account(s) on new server

Create test user accounts

Document credentials securely

8. Federation Configuration
Set up server federation to allow federation with matrix.org and other servers

Configure trusted key servers (already done in your config)

